  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nDisregard the sent transaction in 1-1 chat with 'Send' command which still in 'Pending...' state (in network and so in wallet), - after user re-opens the app the `Outgoing transaction` gets `Confirmed!` status. \nIf to tap on such TX nothing happens, but it because there is no TX in history yet at all so that's expected and a part of another issue.\nThis issue is dedicated to align transaction `Outgoing transaction` status send in 1-1 chat to it's actual status: if TX is not in TX history - we keep showing 'Pending...' status\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nOutgoing transaction keep staying with 'Pending...' status in 1-1 chat after account relogin if it's 'Pending...' in network\n#### Actual behavior\n\nOutgoing transaction gets 'Confirmed... ' status in 1-1 chat after account relogin always\n\nVideo: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1oFzAqlt-47rRII4yNrqJGqOqqamzno6E/view?usp=sharing\n\n\n### Reproduction\n- Open Status and recover an account with funds (UserA)\n- Add UserB in contacts and open 1-1 chat with this contact\n- UserA sends 'Send transaction' with valid amount of ETH/tokens\n- UserB taps `Accept and share address`\n- UserA signs transaction in 1-1 chat\n- UserA re-logins to account and checks transaction status in 1-1 chat\n\n### Additional Information\n- Status version: develop 0.14.0 (2020011702)\n- Operating System: Android and iOS",
